      <section eId="sec_CCRP-921-1">
        <num>CCRP 921.1</num>
        <heading>921.1. Â Notice of decision in criminal appeals</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-921-1__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In addition to the requirements regarding transmission of notice of judgment and copies of decisions under the Uniform Rules of Louisiana Courts of Appeal, when a decision in an appellate court in a criminal appeal is rendered, the clerk of court shall transmit a notice or copy of the decision to the clerk of court from which the appeal was taken and to the Department of Public Safety and Corrections.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-921-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>When a decision of the supreme court is rendered in a criminal appeal, the clerk of court shall transmit a notice or copy of the decision to the clerk of court from which the appeal was taken and to the Department of Public Safety and Corrections.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=919661</p>
